rne/everqst/picon.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Evoker</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>9:01:11 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Community Supporter</FONT><BR><BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg height=200 width=152></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Killing Cobalt Drakes in CS</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have been living in Cobalt Scar for a long time, since level 51 (55 at the time of this post). It's where I go for xp between raids and goofing around. Many wyverns are still blue, but it's getting fairly rare that I can find 3-4 blue ones to quad close enough together for it to be worth doing. So I started killing drakes.<br>
<br>
They are really pretty easy. I haven't worked up the nerve to quad them yet, but single pulls still need most of a bar of mana at 55. I generally lead with Tishan's Discord, and follow through with Atol's. This should be done at maximum range; go farther than you know you have to, and move in until you can cast. If it is one of the drakes that paths near others, I may root it depending on whether that will keep it from running into it's buddies when it comes after me (in other words, give the other time to move away). Then I unload draughts. It works out perfectly (once root breaks or it it is just Atol'd without rooting) to nuke and run just long enough for the draught to recycle, and cast again. This will keep it far enough to prevent it casting. When it's health starts getting low, I make sure I am facing it so I can tell when it will stop chasing me. You can still back away fast enough at jboot speed to keep the proper distance, it just takes a bit longer  backing up. This is to prevent getting so far away that it warps back to it's spawn point; that could be big trouble if it aggros one or more of it's little friends.<br>
<br>
Heh, all that yap to say, &quot;keep your distance, and you will be fine.&quot;</font><P><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Channeler</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:35:33 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Killing Cobalt Drakes in CS</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First thing in killing Drakes is to have a junk buff up then levitate then sow. <br>
<br>
Their AE dispells which ruins your day if sow is the first up.<br>
<br>
Use Atol's and draught of fire ... use temp to check range and you'll have them dead well before you reach SS zone. At 51 they take near a full bar, but drop spells frequently. (or maybe I'm just lucky).<br>
<br>
Since the otters don't help with drakes anymore, If I see more than a couple up (and in my way) I'll kill them first, thus leaving the wyverns open for me and others who are KoS to them.<br>
<br>
I've been able to usher the havoc the drakes had once dealt to me easily since 51. Using PoF I can almost include one with my wyverns. Usually just not enough mana.. a harvest and still not enough... so be careful if you get one with your wyvern pulls.</font><P><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig52.jpg"></p><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=58.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=48.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4><IMG SRC=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=57.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=57.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdan